The <abbr title="Non -Fungible Token">NFTs</abbr> art market has developed at breakneck speed over the last few months, opening up a wide range of possibilities, within which some dominant trends and influential actors are emerging. One of these trends is the replacement of marketpla
ces that are open to all, in which each work is just another image in an infinite grid, by a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\b\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8732741\charrsid9333735 
curated presentation of artworks with a specific discourse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8732741\charrsid9333735  conveyed in the format of an individual artist\rquote s project or a collective exhibition. 
\par Another trend is the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\b\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8732741\charrsid9333735 identification of <abbr title="Non -Fungible Token">NFTs</abbr> with a specific type of image}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8732741\charrsid9333735 , specifically a 3D model or animation with a futuristic aesthetic, along the lines of Beeple\rquote s work, or abstract geometric compositions, also with three-dimensional effects, in the s
tyle of Pak. Finally, the current trend is towards the definitive assimilation of <abbr title="Non -Fungible Token">NFTs</abbr> into the mainstream contemporary art market, as major galleries naturally incorporate this format into their offerings to collectors. Pace, one of the strongest galleri
es globally, has recently launched }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\dbch\af31501\langnp2057\insrsid8732741\charrsid9333735 \hich\af31506\dbch\af31501\loch\f31506 Pace Verso}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8732741\charrsid9333735 , a platform for selling <abbr title="Non -Fungible Token">NFTs</abbr> that, notably, sets prices in dollars and accepts payment by credit card (as well as the main cryptocurrencies), in what can be interpreted as an invitation to 
\'93traditional\'94 collectors who, while they don\rquote t share the enthusiasm of crypto investors, don\rquote t want to be left behind in the acquisition of digital art either.
\par An innovation cannot be said to have been assimilated by the art market until it is adopted by the galleries themselve
s. Now that we are at the point where both Pace and a growing number of other galleries have decided to sell <abbr title="Non -Fungible Token">NFTs</abbr>, it can be considered that non-fungible tokens are going to be as common a format as silkscreen prints, digital prints, photographs or videos
. It is also possible that the enthusiasm for these digital works is nothing more than a speculative bubble that hasn\rquote 
t stopped growing yet (remember that the dot-com bubble lasted five years) and that in a few years many collectors will find that their works are not worth what they paid for them.
\par But in any case, the resilience of the market and the involvement of its most powerful actors bodes a stable future for digital-format art and for records of authenticity and chain-of-ownership in blockchain, or ot
her similar technologies. Whether under their oft-repeated acronym or under a different name, <abbr title="Non -Fungible Token">NFTs</abbr> will continue giving us much to talk about. 
